    <h1>Role Policies Map</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div class=3D"contentLayout2">=20
<div class=3D"columnLayout two-right-sidebar" data-layout=3D"two-right-side=
bar">=20
<div class=3D"cell normal" data-type=3D"normal">=20
<div class=3D"innerCell">=20
<h2 id=3D"RolePoliciesMap-RetrievingtheRolePolicies">Retrieving the Role Po=
licies</h2>
<p>To retrieve the Roles Policies, on a working eZ Platform instance, in de=
v environment open the file <code><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">app/ca=
che/dev/appDevDebugProjectContainer.xml</span></code></p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-not=
e">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-info=
rmation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">If you can not find the file, please =
reload the homepage. The cache will be regenerated.</span></p>
</div>
</div>
<p>Then open it and look for <code>ezpublish.api.role.policy_map</code>, it=
 will look like this:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>ezpublish.api.role.policy_map entry in the app/cache/dev/appDevDebugProj=
ectContainer.xml file</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: xml; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">    &lt;parameter key=3D"ezpublish.api.role.policy_map" type=3D"col=
lection"&gt;
        &lt;parameter key=3D"content" type=3D"collection"&gt;=09=09=09
        &lt;parameter key=3D"read" type=3D"collection"&gt;
        &lt;parameter key=3D"Class"&gt;true&lt;/parameter&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>The 1st sublevel ("content") is a module.</li>
<li>The 2nd sublevel ("read") is a function.</li>
<li>The 3rd sublevel ("Class") is a limitation.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"RolePoliciesMap-Module,functionandlimitations">Module, function a=
nd limitations</h2>
<p>Each Module contains functions, and for each function, you have limitati=
ons. The default values are shown below.</p>
<p>There are 4 modules:</p>
<ul>
<li>content</li>
<li>section</li>
<li>state</li>
<li>user</li>
</ul>
